{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"55603173-20bb-45fe-b1d7-518f4812ffc4","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet restore` and `dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Check for any breaking changes in the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/) and update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f915f33d-9adb-4fa1-ae89-dae0961c9336","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward knowledge question — I don't need to search any codebase. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":287},"id":"36beaf09-0eef-41ae-9d00-ed1bcedb6566","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:02:02.962Z","parentId":"4c949c4f-5c63-4629-8b73-76235dfda6f9"}
